}}</ref> slower songs such as "[[Hurt (song)|Hurt]]" have less lighting effects, while the crowd typically holds up lighters.<ref name="unogateway" />

==Live releases==

Nine Inch Nails has released one album and three videos featuring the live band: ''[[Closure (video)|Closure]]'' in 1997 (double [[VHS]]), ''[[And All That Could Have Been]]'' in 2002 ([[Compact Disc|CD]], VHS, and double [[DVD]]), and ''[[Beside You in Time]]'' in 2007 (DVD, [[HD DVD]], and [[Blu-Ray]]).

''Closure'', a double-VHS video, features live performances from the Self-Destruct Tour, including a performance of "[[Hurt (song)|Hurt]]" with David Bowie during the Dissonance Tour.<ref>{{cite web
  | url = http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1432662/19971202/nine_inch_nails.jhtml
  | publisher = MTV.com
  | accessdate = 2008-02-08
  | title = Nine Inch Nails Releases "Closure"
  | date = [[1997-12-02]]}}</ref>  Since its initial release in 1997, the video has been out of print, and all attempts to re-release the video on DVD have failed.  A deluxe two-disc DVD version of ''Closure'' was delivered to [[Interscope Records]] in 2004, but has been indefinitely delayed.<ref name= "March05">{{cite web
  | url = http://www.nin.com/current/
  | publisher = Nine Inch Nails
  | title = Current
  | date = [[2005-04-15]]
  | archiveurl = http://web.archive.org/web/20050420075258/nin.com/current/
  | archivedate = 2005-04-20
  | accessdate = 2007-08-26}}</ref> However, both discs appeared on [[BitTorrent (protocol)|BitTorrent]] networks in December 2006.<ref>{{cite web
  | url = http://theninhotline.net/news/archives/backissue.php?y=05&m=12#1134412727
  | title = Closer to Closure?
  | publisher = The NIN Hotline
  | date = [[2005-12-12]]
  | accessdate = 2006-11-28}}</ref>  ''And All That Could Have Been'' was released in 2002, as a live CD and double DVD, featuring performances from the Fragility 2.0 tour.  An [[Easter egg (media)|easter egg]] in the DVD version features a performance with [[Marilyn Manson]] at [[Madison Square Garden]] of the songs "[[Starfuckers, Inc.]]" and Manson's "[[The Beautiful People]]."<ref name="AATCHB DVD review" />  In 2007, Nine Inch Nails released ''Beside You in Time'', featuring performances from the Live: With Teeth tour.  The DVD also features rehearsal footage, music videos, and still photographs from the tour.

==Guest artists and collaborations==
Through the years, Reznor has invited many prominent musicians on stage with his band to perform material outside the usual range of Nine Inch Nails songs:

*During [[Lollapalooza]] '91, one of the first exposures the band ever had to a wider audience than its previously [[underground music|underground]] following, [[Jane's Addiction]] members [[Dave Navarro]] and [[Eric Avery]] played guitars alongside [[Gibby Haynes]] and [[Ice-T]] for the last song of the band's set, "[[Head Like a Hole]]".<ref>{{cite web
  | url = http://www.6767.com/archives/2006/10/index.html
  | title = Nine Inch Nails - Head Like a Hole (Lollapalooza 1991)
  | authorlink = Dave Navarro
  | first = Dave
  | last = Navarro
  | publisher = 6767.com
  | date = [[2006-10-04]]
  | accessdate = 2007-02-10}}</ref>
*[Marilyn Manson came on stage at during a concert in 2000 at [[Madison Square Garden]] in 2000 to sing "[[Starfuckers, Inc.]]" and "[[The Beautiful People]]".  This performance is featured as bonus content in the ''[[And All that Could Have Been]]'' DVD.<ref name="AATCHB DVD review" />
* During the Dissonance tour, Nine Inch Nails co-headlined with [[David Bowie]].  Throughout the tour, Nine Inch Nails would perform first and segway into Bowie's band.  The two bands would play a mixture of Nine Inch Nails and David Bowie songs.  Nine Inch Nails would eventually leave the stage and Bowie and his band would continue with their own set.<ref name="Dissonance 1" /><ref name="Dissonance 2" />
* During the Live: With Teeth amphitheater tour, Nine Inch Nails and [[Peter Murphy (musician)|Peter Murphy]] of [[Bauhaus (band)|Bauhaus]] performed the [[Pere Ubu (band)|Pere Ubu]] song "[[Final Solution (disambiguation)|Final Solution]]", which was also a solo hit for Murphy. For the last show they collaborated to cover [[Joy Division]]'s "Dead Souls", which Nine Inch Nails has regularly played since 1994.  Also during this tour Reznor, Murphy, and some other musicians performed four unique sets of their favorite songs on radio stations around the country.<ref>{{cite web
  | url = http://www.nin.com/current/radioshows/index.html
  | title = Live Radio Performances
  | publisher = Nine Inch Nails
  | accessdate = 2007-02-10
  | archiveurl = http://web.archive.org/web/20070224171243/http://www.nin.com/current/radioshows/index.html
  | archivedate = 2007-02-24}}</ref>

